Wilson Score Ranking

The weighted score uses the Wilson score interval - a statistical method that balances win rate with sample size.

Score = Lower bound of 95% confidence interval

This means KOLs with few predictions are penalized (less certainty), while consistent performers with many predictions rank higher.

Example: 60% with 20 signals ranks higher than 80% with 3 signals.
